Create a `.vscode/mcp.json` file in your workspace root:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "my-mcp-server": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `type: "stdio"` — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.
- `command` / `args` — runs `dotnet run --project <path>` to start your server.
- Make sure your server reads from stdin and writes to stdout (standard MCP stdio transport).

After saving, open the Copilot chat panel in agent mode — VS Code will automatically discover and start the server.
